> <i>You get to the end and all of a sudden the }();</i><p>With most code conventions, you wrap immediately invoked function expressions (IIFEs) in parens:<p><pre><code>  var foo = (function () {
    ...
  }());
</code></pre>
The only purpose of those extra parens is to act as marker.<p>Well, with block scope (`let` & `const`), IIFEs aren&#x27;t really needed anymore.
